HACL* Vendored C Sources
========================

Source:  https://github.com/hacl-star/hacl-star
Commit:  504c298
Extract: dist/gcc-compatible/

These files are a curated subset of the HACL* formally F*-verified C crypto
library, extracted from dist/gcc-compatible/ for use as the primary runtime
crypto implementation in the UmbraVOX main build (milestones M13.15.8-M13.15.14).

License: MIT / Apache-2.0
See: ../../contrib/oracles/src/hacl-star/LICENSE

DO NOT modify these files. If updates are needed, regenerate from the
upstream source tree and re-copy using the same procedure.

Algorithm sources
-----------------
Hacl_Hash_SHA2.h / Hacl_Hash_SHA2.c    -- SHA-256 and SHA-512
Hacl_Hash_SHA3.h / Hacl_Hash_SHA3.c    -- SHA-3 / Keccak / SHAKE
Hacl_Chacha20.h  / Hacl_Chacha20.c     -- ChaCha20 stream cipher
Hacl_MAC_Poly1305.h / Hacl_MAC_Poly1305.c -- Poly1305 MAC
Hacl_HMAC.h      / Hacl_HMAC.c         -- HMAC (over any hash)
Hacl_HKDF.h      / Hacl_HKDF.c         -- HKDF (over HMAC)
Hacl_Hash_Base.h / Hacl_Hash_Base.c    -- Shared hash base types

Support headers
---------------
Hacl_Streaming_Types.h  -- Streaming API types
Hacl_SHA2_Types.h       -- SHA-2 internal types
Hacl_Krmllib.h          -- KaRaMeL runtime (integer ops, endianness)
Hacl_Spec.h             -- Spec types
lib_memzero0.h          -- Secure memory zeroing
Lib_Memzero0.c          -- Secure memory zeroing implementation

KaRaMeL runtime headers (krml/)
--------------------------------
krml/internal/types.h           -- Fixed-width integer types
krml/internal/target.h          -- Compiler portability macros
krml/internal/builtin.h         -- Compiler built-ins
krml/internal/callconv.h        -- Calling convention macros
krml/internal/compat.h          -- Compatibility macros
krml/lowstar_endianness.h       -- Endianness helpers
krml/c_endianness.h             -- C endianness macros
krml/FStar_UInt128.h            -- 128-bit integer support
krml/FStar_UInt_8_16_32_64.h    -- Fixed-width integer helpers

Bridge files (bridge_*.c)
--------------------------
The bridge_*.c files in this directory are UmbraVOX-specific thin wrappers
that adapt HACL* entry points to the function signatures expected by the
Haskell FFI layer. They are not part of the upstream HACL* distribution.
